The paper deals with data structures for point location queries in planar subdivisions, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also introduces a new data structure that is asymptotically as fast as optimal structures, which suggests that it may be related to data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The paper also mentions probability distributions and adapting to query sequences, which suggests that it may be related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.SI).
